@harrybin815 luarocks automatically installs the dependent files at the time of installation, so there is no need to install `dependencies` directory.
https://github.com/apache/skywalking-nginx-lua/blob/master/rockspec/skywalking-nginx-lua-0.1-0.rockspec#L14

`client.lua` and `tracer.lua` are showing how to use this library, and you may need to implement your own version.

Take a look at the storage provider, such as `StorageModuleElasticsearchProvider#start`.  Storage installation happens there
```java
StorageEsInstaller installer = new StorageEsInstaller(getManager(), config);
installer.install(elasticSearchClient);
```

The OAL engine is required to process before that, but currently, there is no guarantee, right?
